A man has died after he collapsed while fishing off rocks on the West Coast near Cape Town, the National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) said on Sunday. NSRI spokesman Craig Lambinon said NSRI Melkbosstrand off-duty crewman Terence Lawson was fishing at Kreeftebaai between Bloubergstrand and Melkbosstrand on Saturday when he was alerted to a commotion nearby. On investigation he found a local man had collapsed unconscious while fishing in among rocks. The man was breathless and found to be pulseless , and Lawson initiated cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) efforts assisted by friends and bystanders. A doctor who happened to be nearby also assisted and SA Paramedic Services responded, but sadly the man was declared deceased suspected to be from natural causes. Police assisted the family and an inquest docket had been opened, he said. African News Agency (ANA)